sec.p:
We parsed full-length human-isolate spikes encoding unique proteins from this sequence set (see 
https://github.com/jbloomlab/CoV_229E_antigenic_drift/blob/master/results/get_parse_spikes.md), used mafft (Katoh and Standley, 2013) to align the protein sequences, and used a custom Python script (
https://github.com/jbloomlab/CoV_229E_antigenic_drift/blob/master/prot_to_codon_alignment.py
) to build a codon alignment from the protein alignment (File S1). We used GARD (Kosakovsky Pond et al., 2006; Spielman et al., 2019) to screen for recombination (see tanglegram in Figure S2 and code at 
https://github.com/jbloomlab/CoV_229E_antigenic_drift/blob/master/results/gard_tanglegram.md
).
